# BrainTrust Circle — UX Expert Note (Design Iterations)

## Purpose
Concise UX audit + information architecture for the desktop app foundation. Outcome: confirm layout, then proceed to theme and component build.

## Quick audit of current design system (default_ui_darkmode.css)
- Strengths
  - Uses OKLCH tokens for core colors, spacing, typography; responsive utilities; focus-visible; reduced motion variant.
  - Solid primitives: cards, buttons, inputs, tabs, badges, list, empty states.
- Issues to address (before component build)
  - Replace hardcoded hex in tabs (e.g., `#f8f9fa`, `#1a1a1a`) with tokens to keep themes coherent.
  - Re-evaluate `--primary`: currently near-white; primary on dark should read as accent, not almost-white. Propose moving accent/primary to a non-blue hue (avoid indigo/blue), e.g., violet/amber/emerald.
  - Ensure focus ring meets 3:1 on dark backgrounds; current `--ring` is gray—verify contrast on all interactive states.
  - Add explicit semantic tokens: `--success`, `--warning`, `--info` with matching text and bg pairs for badges/toasts.
  - Normalize button states (hover/active/disabled) with tokenized elevations and not raw rgba whites.

Recommended token adjustments (illustrative, not applied yet):
- `--primary: oklch(0.72 0.2 275);`  // purple-violet, non-blue, high chroma
- `--accent: oklch(0.80 0.12 145);`  // emerald accent for confirmations
- Add `--focus: oklch(0.78 0.19 275);` and use for focus-visible outline

## Information architecture (high-level)
- Global top bar: workspace switcher, search/command, status, quick actions.
- Left sidebar: Specialist Library (browse, pin, filter), Teams, Templates.
- Center: Conversation Feed (single thread, multi-agent participation) + message controls.
- Right panel: Context/Memory Inspector, Task/Project details, Integrations.
- Bottom: Composer (input, tools, send), with expand-to-advanced controls.

