Responsive behavior
- ≤1024px: collapse right panel into a slide-over; keep feed full-width.
- ≤768px: left sidebar becomes a drawer; bottom tab bar for primary sections.

## Core interactions
- Message actions (hover or tap hold): copy, pin, quote, create task, summarize, fork to sandbox.
- Multi-AI: toggle which AI responds next, or aggregate; show source labels per message.
- Composer enhancements: slash commands, variable chips (project, deadline), token count, send modifiers (Shift+Enter newline, Enter send).
- Task extraction: Super Organizer proposes tasks with priority badges; confirm → auto-schedule.

## Microcopy principles
- Action-first, low-ambiguity labels (“Create task,” “Schedule,” “Summarize”).
- Surface consequences in UI (“Will post to Calendar”).
- Keep timestamps relative by default; absolute on hover.

## Accessibility & motion
- Keyboard: full traversal (Tab order: top bar → left → feed → right → composer). Provide skip-to-composer.
- Focus: 2px outline using `--focus` token; never rely on color alone.
- Contrast: meet 4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for UI components and focus.
- Motion: respect `prefers-reduced-motion`; no essential info via animation only.

## Acceptance criteria for layout sign-off
- The five regions exist and resize predictably.
- Left/right panels dock/collapse; state persists.
- Composer supports basic attachments and tool affordances.
- Feed supports per-message actions and shows the speaking agent clearly.

